@skottmckay We make use of #2 in our custom EP ([link](https://github.com/pranav-prakash/onnxruntime-riscv/blob/2021-04-02/onnxruntime/core/providers/systolic/fusion/qlinearconv_relu_fuse.cc) to the node-fusion we define in our EP)

> ONNX type/shape inferencing would have already happened prior to fusion

Is this still true if Level 3 graph transforms are performed? I observed that these are performed after partitioning, and this was the case motivating the creation of the PR – I recall that the outputs of fused ops had no shape info after the shape-inference pass following level 3 transforms (but it's been a few months so I might need to double check)

@skottmckay
(We use our own nhwc transformer – not the upstream one – but last I checked the upstream one doesn't set shape info for nodeargs either).

So just to clarify, is the suggested solution to set shape info in the transformer itself when processing a fused node? That works for me (but it feels more like a workaround – I still feel allowing the `inference_function` to be manually set when creating a fused node is a cleaner solution; albeit either achieves the same end result).
